09/05/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The second world conference on inter-religious and inter-cultural dialogue closed in the town of Ohrid on Saturday (May 8th). 
The two-day forum brought together 500 representatives of religious communities, experts and politicians from 30 countries. 
Participants adopted a final declaration, voicing their commitment to strengthening peace and co-operation through constant dialogue and exchange of expertise. 
They also agreed to encourage cultural events and activities aimed at promoting tolerance and co-existence. 
(Sitel, MIA, Makfax - 08/05/10)
